19.04	Peter_Lombard	Peter Lombard	Peter Lombard (rather Peter the Lombard) or Petrus Lombardus (c. 1096, Novara, Lombardy - August 21/22, 1164, Paris, France) was a scholastic theologian and bishop and author of Four Books of Sentences, which became the standard textbook of theology, for which he earned the accolade Magister Sententiarum.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/ae/PeterLombar01Medieval.png/198px-PeterLombar01Medieval.png
